<title>USA: Open Market completes purchase of Folio.</title>
<headline>Open Market completes purchase of Folio.</headline>
<dateline>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. 1997-03-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Open Market Inc a provider of Internet commerce management software, said Friday it has completed its acquisition of Folio Corp, a subsidiary of Reed Elsevier Plc, for $45 million.</p>
<p>The purchase consideration, said the company, will be paid in the form of $25 million in equity, $15 million in cash and $5 million in either cash and/or equity depending on certain post-closing events.</p>
<p>The acquisition will be accounted for as a purchase with a significant portion of the purchase price being allocated to in-process research and development and expensed at the close of the current quarter.</p>
